                                                                  9655 1451
  2) Two-component exciton model/14/                              9655 1451
    * Global parametrization of Koning-Duijvestijn/15/            9655 1451
      was used.                                                   9655 1451
    * Gamma emission channel/16/ was added to simulate direct     9655 1451
      and semi-direct capture reaction.                           9655 1451
                                                                  9655 1451
  3) Hauser-Feshbach statistical model                            9655 1451
    * Moldauer width fluctuation correction/17/ was included.     9655 1451
    * Neutron, gamma and fission decay channel were included.     9655 1451
    * Transmission coefficients of neutrons were taken from       9655 1451
      coupled channel calculation in Table 1.                     9655 1451
    * The level scheme of the target is shown in Table 2.         9655 1451
    * Level density formula of constant temperature and Fermi-gas 9655 1451
      model were used with shell energy correction and collective 9655 1451
      enhancement factor. Parameters are shown in Table 3.        9655 1451
    * Fission channel:                                            9655 1451
      Double humped fission barriers were assumed.                9655 1451
      Fission barrier penetrabilities were calculated with        9655 1451
      Hill-Wheler formula/18/. Fission barrier parameters were    9655 1451
      shown in Table 4. Transition state model was used and       9655 1451
      continuum levels are assumed above the saddles. The level   9655 1451
      density parameters for inner and outer saddles are shown in 9655 1451
      Tables 5 and 6, respectively.                               9655 1451
    * Gamma-ray strength function of Kopecky et al/19/,/20/       9655 1451
